  "title": "Instant search with infinite scroll repeats records",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nInstant search page with infinite scroll enabled, repeats records/products randomly after 4-5 pages\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nGo to https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?selectedStory=InfiniteHits.default\r\nClick on \"show more\" button 4 to 5 times and observe the results loaded. You should see that some products have repeated.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nRecords/products should not repeat.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots 🖥**\r\n<img width=\"1095\" alt=\"screenshot 2018-05-23 10 10 07\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1058144/40411845-e933d5e4-5e71-11e8-89fc-adbfbfb8b649.png\">\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\n - OS: MacOS\r\n - Browser: Chrome\r\n - Version: 66.0.3359.181\r\n",
